These are Puzzles for 1x2 Level 3

.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-1::.
2 different brands of cigars are smoked: fonseca, oliveros
1. the oliveros-smoker is on the far left or far right##3
2. the fonseca-smoker is on the right of the oliveros-smoker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |   2   |
| Cigar   | oliveros | fonseca |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-2::.
The people use 2 different means of transport: snowmobile, quad-bike
1. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left or right of the person driving the quad-bike##3
2. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person driving the snowmobile##1

.:: Answer ::.
|       |     1     |      2      |
| Transport   | snowmobile | quad-bike |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-3::.
City: miami, rome
1. the person traveling to rome is on the left or right of the person traveling to miami##3
2. the person traveling to rome is on the left of the person traveling to miami##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1      |    2    |
| City   | rome | miami |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x2-Level-3-4::.
